data.name: Creamy Clam Chowder
data.quickTastyDescription: A rich and creamy chowder filled with tender clams, potatoes, and a hint of smokiness from bacon.
detailedCookingInstructions: In a large pot, cook the chopped bacon over medium heat until crispy. Remove and set aside, leaving the bacon fat in the pot.
Add the chopped onion and celery to the pot, cooking until softened, about 5 minutes.
Stir in the diced potatoes, clam juice, and thyme. Bring to a boil, then reduce heat and simmer until the potatoes are tender, about 15 minutes.
Add the fresh clams and cook until they open, about 5 minutes. Discard any clams that do not open.
Once the clams are cooked, stir in the heavy cream and butter. Heat through, but do not boil.
Season with salt and black pepper to taste. Serve hot, garnished with crispy bacon.
